dex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Sept 19, 2024</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent wide\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104hil1665702649700.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/hil1665702649700.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/hil1665702649700.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"hil1665702649700\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n      Parsing Nested Associative Lists\n </h1>\n<div class=\"body conbody\" id=\"hil1665702649700__parsing_nested_associative_lists_56633\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">Several ProcScript functions return an associative list that can hold several levels\n    of nested lists. The example ProcScript function <code class=\"ph codeph\">showidlist</code> can be called to\n    parse such lists. </p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"hil1665702649700__p_d16757e1_d16758e1_d16759e1\">The <code class=\"ph codeph\">showidlist</code> function parses an\n      associative list returned by <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$procerrorcontext</span>.</p>\n<div class=\"code-toolbar\"><pre class=\"pre language-plaintext\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-plaintext\">function showidlist\nparams\n string list : IN\n string level : IN\nendparams\nvariables\n string item\n string id\n string nextlist\n numeric index\nendvariables\n; end if we do not have an associative item\nif ($idpart(list) = $valuepart(list))\n return\nendif\nindex = 0 \nrepeat\n index = index + 1\n getitem item, list, index\n if ($status = 0)\n break\n endif\n \n id = $idpart(item)\n nextlist = $valuepart(item)\n putmess \"Item %%level%%%.%%index%%%: ID = %%id%%% VAL = %%nextlist%%%\"\n call showidlist(nextlist, \"%%level%%%.%%index%%%\") \nuntil (1=0)\nend</code></pre><div class=\"toolbar\"><div class=\"toolbar-item\"><button class=\"copy-to-clipboard-button\" data-copy-state=\"copy\" type=\"button\"><span>Copy</span></button></div></div></div>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"hil1665702649700__p_d16760e1_d16761e1_d16762e1\">The displayed output depends on the input list.</p>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_3613491\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_3613491\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "Parsing Nested Associative Lists Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Sept 19, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Parsing Nested Associative Lists Several ProcScript functions return an associative list that can hold several levels of nested lists. The example ProcScript function showidlist can be called to parse such lists. The showidlist function parses an associative list returned by $procerrorcontext . function showidlist params string list : IN string level : IN endparams variables string item string id string nextlist numeric index endvariables ; end if we do not have an associative item if ($idpart(list) = $valuepart(list)) return endif index = 0 repeat index = index + 1 getitem item, list, index if ($status = 0) break endif id = $idpart(item) nextlist = $valuepart(item) putmess \"Item %%level%%%.%%index%%%: ID = %%id%%% VAL = %%nextlist%%%\" call showidlist(nextlist, \"%%level%%%.%%index%%%\") until (1=0) end Copy The displayed output depends on the input list. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}